thread.title: Leonard Fournette streak broken; Alabama's Derrick Henry SEC Offensive Player of the Week
thread.title_full: Leonard Fournette streak broken; Alabama's Derrick Henry SEC Offensive Player of the Week | NOLA.com

author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Leonard Fournette streak broken; Alabama's Derrick Henry SEC Offensive Player of the Week
text:
Leonard Fournette has a streak of three straight 200-yard rushing games going. But Alabama running back broke his hold on the SEC Offensive Player of the Week honor.
Henry rushed for 148 yards and a touchdown in the Tide's 38-10 rout of Georgia Saturday. Fournette, who won the honor the last three weeks, rushed for 233 yards and three scores against Eastern Michigan, becoming the first SEC player with three consecutive 200-yard games.
Henry had a scoring run of 30 yards and four carries of at least 10 yards.
Florida linebacker Antonio Morrison was the SEC Defensive Player of the Week as he totaled 16 tackles in the Gators' victory against No. 3 Ole Miss. Auburn return specialist Rudy Ford won the Special Teams POW honor with two kickoff returns for 81 yards. He also had 14 tackles. For more information go here .
Here is a list of the other awards:
OL Sebastian Tretola, Arkansas, Offensive Lineman
WR Calvin Ridley, Alabama, Freshman POW
DE Myles Garrett, Texas A&M, Defensive Lineman
